⚙️ 4. What Traefik actually looks like

Inside the cluster, you define:

Example (IngressRoute or Ingress)
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
kind: Ingress
metadata:
  name: app
spec:
  rules:
    - host: app.company.com
      http:
        paths:
          - path: /
            pathType: Prefix
            backend:
              service:
                name: my-app
                port:
                  number: 80
Or with TLS passthrough (important)

If you’re doing TLS passthrough, Traefik must be configured like:

TCP router
based on SNI

Example concept:

tcp:
  routers:
    app:
      rule: "HostSNI(`app.company.com`)"
      service: app-service
      tls:
        passthrough: true

  services:
    app-service:
      loadBalancer:
        servers:
          - address: "my-app:443"

👉 This is what makes the chain work

